<SCRIPT LANGUAGE="JavaScript" SRC="js/DataValidation.js"></SCRIPT><B CLASS="HeadlineText">The Gifts of the Halflings</B><BR><BR><H4><FONT face=Garamond>
<P></FONT><FONT face=Garamond><FONT size=2><FONT size=2><FONT face=Garamond><EM><SPAN class=headers>Xanthe`s Earring/PoTC - The Gifts of the Elves</SPAN> </EM></FONT></FONT><FONT face=Garamond size=1><EM></EM></FONT></FONT></FONT></P></H4>
<P><FONT face=Garamond><FONT size=2><FONT face=Garamond><EM>The first three gifts come to us from elven lands. Original writeup courtesy of Xanthe Ravenwolf. Known trivials are now included.</EM></FONT></P>
<H4>
<P></FONT>First Gift of the Halflings</FONT></P></H4>
<P><A href="http://www.eqtraders.com/items/show_item.php?item=1767&amp;menustr="><FONT color=#000000 face=Garamond size=1>Lotus Pie</FONT></A><FONT face=Garamond size=1> </FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Lotus Pie (miraculous meal, CHA 9) = Thick Lotus Paste + Clump of Dough + Pie Tin (oven/spit, <I>baking trivial 236, yield 6 pies</I>) </FONT></LI></UL>
<P><FONT size=1><FONT face=Garamond><I>Other combines/items that you will need</I> </FONT></FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Thick Lotus Paste (meal, CHA 9) = 1 Sweet Lotus Sap (*or* sticky lotus sap *or* soft lotus petals *or* black lotus stem) + Allspice + Flour + Cream (oven/spit, <I>baking trivial &gt;101 &lt;=141</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Cream = Benzoin + 2 Milk (unstacked) + Dairy Spoon (mixing bowl, <I>baking trivial 83</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Dairy Spoon = 2 Metal Bits (unstacked) + Scalar Mold + water (forge, <I>smithing trivial 67</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>clump of dough = 1 Egg of whatever kind + Milk + Flour (mixing bowl, <I>baking trivial 17</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Pie tin can be either smithed or made via pottery </FONT></LI></UL>
<P><FONT face=Garamond size=1><I>(sweet lotus sap, sticky lotus sap, black lotus stem and soft lotus petals are all dropped by the deep cavern lotuses in Fungus Grove. Drops off the cave lotus in Dulak will NOT work) </I></FONT></P>
<H4><FONT face=Garamond>Second Gift of the Halflings</FONT></H4>
<P><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Note that halfings <I>REALLY</I> love their food, and many of the below recipes yield more than one on a success. Given the difficulty of the final combine, this is a good thing, as you will likely lose many to failures, but, for example, don't go overboard when making marmalade, or you'll find that you have no room for the rest of the ingredients. Also the picnic is a large item, so keep room in one of your bigger containers free for it. </FONT>
<P><A href="http://www.eqtraders.com/items/show_item.php?item=1139&amp;menustr="><FONT color=#000000 face=Garamond size=1>Misty Thicket Picnic</FONT></A><FONT face=Garamond size=1> </FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Misty Thicket Picnic (miraculous meal, STR 5, STA 5, WIS 5, INT 5, size: large) = 1 Picnic Basket + 1 Marmalade Sandwich + 1 Jumjum Spiced Beer + 1 Jumjum Salad + 1 Royal Mints + 1 Mature Cheese + 2 (unstacked) Jumjum Cake Slices (oven, <I>baking trivial &gt;250, yield 4 picnics</I>) </FONT></LI></UL>
<P><FONT size=1><FONT face=Garamond><I>Other combines/items that you will need</I> </FONT></FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Picnic Basket = 1 Woven Mandrake + 1 Steel Boning (sewing kit, <I>tailoring trivial 76, yield 10</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Woven Mandrake = 2 Mandrake Roots (unstacked) (sewing kit, <I>tailoring trivial 66</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Steel Boning = 1 Small Brick of Ore + 1 File + water (forge, <I>smithing trivial 37</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Marmalade Sandwich = 1 Apricot Marmalade + 1 Loaf of Bread (mixing bow, <I>baking trivial 99, yield 12 sandwiches</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Apricot Marmalade = 3 Frosting (unstacked) + 1 Fruit (oven, <I>baking trivial 99, yield 6 marmalade</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Jumjum Spiced Beer = Barley + Hops + Spices + Water + Bottle + Jumjum Stalk (brew barrel, <I>brewing trivial 162, yield 10 beer</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Jumjum Salad = 1 Vegetables + 1 Lettuce + 1 Fennel + 1 Jumjum Stalk (mixing bowl, <I>baking trivial 142, yield 10 salads</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Royal Mints = Eucalyptus + Frosting (mixing bowl, <I>baking trivial 76, yield 10 mints</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Mature Cheese = Rennet + 2 Milk (unstacked) + Dairy Spoon (mixing bowl, <I>baking trivial 84</I>, <I>yield 10 cheese</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Dairy Spoon = 2 Metal Bits (unstacked) + Scalar Mold + water (forge, <I>smithing trivial 86</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Jumjum Cake Slice = 1 Jumjum Cake (oven/spit, <I>baking trivial &lt;=152, yields 10 slices</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Jumjum Cake = Jumjum Stalk + Frosting + Clump of Dough + Winter Chocolate + Cake Round (spit/oven, <I>baking trivial 166</I>, <I>yield 20 cake</I>s) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Winter Chocolate = 1 Brownie Parts + 2 Frosting (unstacked) (mixing bowl, <I>baking trivial 95</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>brownie parts drop off pretty much any brownie (Lesser Faydark, Greater Faydark, Steamfont?), as well as from Nillipus in Rivervale </FONT></LI></UL>
<H4><FONT face=Garamond>Third Gift of the Halflings</FONT></H4>
<P><A href="http://www.eqtraders.com/items/show_item.php?item=1140&amp;menustr="><FONT color=#000000 face=Garamond size=1>Lucky Cabbage</FONT></A><FONT face=Garamond size=1> </FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Lucky Cabbage <I>(meal, CHA 10)</I> = 1 Wild Cabbage + Blessed Dust of Karana (mixing bowl, <I>baking trivial 182</I>) </FONT></LI></UL>
<P><FONT size=1><FONT face=Garamond><I>Other combines that you will need</I> </FONT></FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Blessed Dust of Karana = 1 Imbued Plains Pebble + Celestial Essence + Jar of Acid (kiln, <I>pottery trivial 103</I>) </FONT>
<LI><FONT face=Garamond size=1>Celestial Essence = 1 Celestial Solvent + 1 High End Research component (mortar and pestle, <I>no-fail combine</I>) </FONT></LI></UL><BR><BR><BR clear=all>
